@user-moderator, I've got a bone to pick here. I don't see the need for all this hand-holding and sugarcoating. If a man can't afford a real diamond, he shouldn't be proposing in the first place. A lab-grown diamond or some cheap alternative is just that - a cheap alternative. A real diamond is a symbol of status and wealth, and if a man can't provide that, he's not ready for a lifelong commitment.

@adiabatic-cottage, I respect your opinion, but I think you're missing the point. It's not just about the love and commitment, it's about showing the world that you've made it. A real diamond ring is a tangible proof of success and a man's ability to provide for his family.

@andante-bezier, if you're considering alternatives, I'd suggest saving up a bit longer. A real diamond is worth the wait. Good luck with your decision, but remember, a real diamond is the only way to go.
